  "body": "Seems to be another Windows pathing issue somewhere in `helm template`.\r\n\r\nOn Windows, this example works fine:\r\n\r\n```\r\nPS C:\\Users\\mafishe\\code> helm fetch stable/traefik --untar\r\nPS C:\\Users\\mafishe\\code> helm template .\\traefik\\\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut as soon as you tack on the `-x` flag, it renders nothing:\r\n\r\n```\r\nPS C:\\Users\\mafishe\\code> helm template .\\traefik\\ -x templates\\deployment.yaml\r\nPS C:\\Users\\mafishe\\code> helm template .\\traefik\\ -x templates/deployment.yaml\r\nPS C:\\Users\\mafishe\\code>\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis appears to work just fine on linux though.",
